article.headline: Northwestern St. 79, Nicholls State 70
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. (AP) -- Luke Rogers scored 13 points and Southland Conference leader Northwestern State never trailed as the Demons defeated Nicholls State 79-70 Thursday night. Clifton Lee added 12 points for Northwestern State (18-6, 11-1), Tyronn Mitchell had 11 and Colby Bargeman chipped in 10. The Demons jumped out to an 18-4 lead. The spread got no bigger than 16 the rest of the way, but the Colonels (8-15, 4-8) never got closer than five points. When they did, at 47-42 early in the second half, Northwestern responded with a 15-4 run. Stefan Blaszczynski led Nicholls with 20 points. Adonis Gray added 19 and Cyril had 12.
